<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-04-16T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-04-16T07:00:00-05:00" n="81" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d81">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1039/2249:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sterling</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-04-16T13:00:00+01:00">April 16,
                                    1940—1 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received April 16—10:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>282. Following telephoned by Mrs. Harriman at noon.</p>
                        <p>All members of the Norwegian Foreign Office have left for Stockholm.
                            Marshal of the Court has arrived at Salen where the Crown Princess with
                            her children are staying. He states that all the members of the Royal
                            Family are well and may go to Stockholm.</p>
                        <p>She now knows whereabouts of Norwegian Government across Swedish border.
                            The roads are open and when Losey<note n="22" xml:id="d81fn22">Capt.
                                Robert M. Losey, Assistant Military Attaché in Norway and
                                Sweden.</note> returns to her at Salen she will proceed with him to
                            Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sterling</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>